[*] There's an issues, where the parts of the text that are practiced less often, will have smaller data points. These parts will have very extreme numbers (let's say a part towards the end of the text, only seen once, is either 100 percent correct or 100 percent incorrect. This ruins the ranges seen in the heatmap). Therefore, there should be a limit, where the heat maps are drawn for ranges of the text that are seen across at least 50 percent of the attempts. 